        "content": "<p>Hi! I was wondering what the reason is that the <code>selinux-fix</code> feature flag of <code>cranelift-jit</code> is not enabled by default. Does it not work for all platforms or is there a performance penalty?</p>",
        "id": 564720993,
        "sender_full_name": "Terts Diepraam",
        "timestamp": 1766157793
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I found this issue about it, but maybe you've found more reasons in the meantime? <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/4986\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/4986</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/4986\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/4986\" title=\"Always use mmap instead of posix_memalign in cranelift-jit 路 Issue #4986 路 bytecodealliance/wasmtime\">Always use mmap instead of posix_memalign in cranelift-jit 路 Issue #4986 路 bytecodealliance/wasmtime</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">This currently behind the selinux-fix feature flag. SELinux doesn't allow making parts of the heap executable. In addition it seems that there is an issue in multithreaded environments causing perm...</div></div></div>",
        "id": 564722261,
        "sender_full_name": "Terts Diepraam",
        "timestamp": 1766158123
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not aware on any other reasons than that.</p>",
        "id": 566168982,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1767466234
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm personally still in favor of always using mmap.</p>",
        "id": 566168990,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1767466258
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've personally used <a href=\"https://lib.rs/crates/talc\"><code>talc</code></a> on top of <code>mmap</code> to make an allocator for executable code, it works well enough.</p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://lib.rs/crates/talc\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/22eb744fc11c84b94801a3128b00638f4e5063e4/68747470733a2f2f6c69622e72732f6f672f632f74616c632e706e67&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://lib.rs/crates/talc\" title=\"talc\">talc</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">A fast and flexible allocator for no_std and WebAssembly</div></div></div>",
        "id": 566171302,
        "sender_full_name": "Amanieu",
        "timestamp": 1767468914
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Alright, thank you! I'll try enabling it by default for Roto then.</p>",
